<% content_for :title, "About" %>

<div class="page-container">
  <h1 class="heading-page">About Landscape Guessr</h1>

  <p class="text-gray-600 text-lg">
    Landscape Guessr is a geography guessing game built for CS-397 at Northwestern University.
    You're shown photographs of natural landmarks from around the world and challenged to place them on a map.
    The closer your guess, the higher your score &mdash; up to 5,000 points per round.
  </p>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2 class="heading-section">The team</h2>
    <ul class="divide-y divide-gray-100 border border-gray-100 rounded-lg overflow-hidden">
      <li class="px-5 py-4 bg-white text-sm font-medium">Jay Rao</li>
      <li class="px-5 py-4 bg-white text-sm font-medium">Andre Shportko</li>
      <li class="px-5 py-4 bg-white text-sm font-medium">Mirai Duintjer Tebbens Nishioka</li>
      <li class="px-5 py-4 bg-white text-sm font-medium">Leyla Latifova</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-3">
    <h2 class="heading-section">Source code</h2>
    <p class="muted">
      This project is open source.
      <%= link_to "View the repository on GitHub",
            "https://github.com/NU-CS-Software-Studio-Spring-26/project-landscape_guessr",
            class: "text-blue-600 hover:underline font-medium" %>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-3">
    <h2 class="heading-section">Legal</h2>
    <p class="muted">
      Landscape photos are sourced from Wikimedia Commons and other public-domain or freely-licensed collections.
      Map tiles are provided by <%= link_to "MapTiler", "https://www.maptiler.com", class: "text-blue-600 hover:underline" %>.
      This application is a student project and is not affiliated with GeoGuessr or any commercial product.
    </p>
  </section>
</div>
